      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ANDY WIN (2) has established himself as one of the premier jumpers in training, producing big wins at his past 2 hurdle starts, including an emphatic 11-length romp at Warrnambool a fortnight ago. He is facing 3 other rivals, and the hat-trick beckons. ARDAKAN (3) has gone to another level this prep, following a strong runner-up performance behind the top pick with a commanding 15-length hurdle victory at Warrnambool last time out. He is the main threat to the favourite. GAMBU (4) has been kept ticking over on the flat since his last jumps appearance and was a sound third at Wodonga 15-days ago. He can finish third here as well. THE CUNNING FOX (1) has been competing on the flat at his past two outings and now returns to the jumps, and he does have a recent trial win over hurdles. He is not out of this.",
